  "biography_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">No biographical information exists for a philosopher named Damippus. The name appears in historical sources, but in other contexts. One was a Spartan mentioned by Plutarch during the Peloponnesian War, and another was a Syracusan envoy in 212 BCE.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">The existence of a philosophical treatise attributed to Damippus is unattested in standard digital repositories and major reference works for ancient Greek literature.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">Damippus holds no established significance as a philosopher. He is absent from all canonical lists of pre-Socratic, Socratic, or other Classical philosophical figures.</p>\n</div>",
